The app provides the following data for each country in the United States by State and their locations:
- snowfall;
- snowdepth;
- snowdensity;
- snowwater equivalent.


Access to these data supports the Federal Emergency Management Agency's (FEMA) need for near real-time observations used in assessing requests for disaster assistance. 


The app also allows to:
- Search in more than 15.000 snow stations available;
- Check the snow stations directly from the map;
- Search snow stations by name, description, region, US state, or geolocation (latitude, longitude - GPS location service supported)
- Save your favorite snow stations;
- If offline, lastly available aviations observations will always be accessible for every stations
- Coverage United States and Canada.

